The paper discusses the construction of a retrieval and recognition engine for historical handwritten document collections, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR), computer vision (CV), natural language processing (NLP), deep learning (DL), and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, which deals with information retrieval. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning for this task, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (computer vision), cs.CL (natural language processing), or cs.DL (deep learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the technical realization, work flow, quality and quantity of material, industrialization and scalability, human effort, algorithms, object of recognition, processing pipeline, performance, and compositionality, which could also fit into sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.HC (human-computer interaction).
